replies.body:
To answer your question:
Supports do not CS. They build a support item that generates gold. Either {{item:3301}} {{item:3302}} {{item:3303}}
You also take the gold generation masteries that are in the "Utility" Tree.
Supports aren't meant to buy "good items", thats why  they are supports. They are there to provide help to the team through CC (like stuns,roots etc) and keep their team alive or catch the enemy so the team can kill them.

Support Zyra is one of the supports that builds damage rather then stuff that helps the team.

What you should build is: Mobility Boots or Sorcer Shoes, Support item (seen above), Sightstone (not needed when playing bots), You can then build damage. Something like, Liandries, Rabadon Deathcap, Twin Shadows, maybe a Banner of Command if you really want to.
If you really have trouble with running out of mana, build a tear first item {{item:3070}}

